🔐 Spear Phishing Simulation using Machine Learning
📌 Overview

This project simulates real-world spear phishing attacks using machine learning to improve cybersecurity awareness and detection. It generates targeted phishing scenarios by analyzing user data and mimicking attacker behavior.

🚀 Features
Automated data collection using Python + Selenium
Machine learning-based classification of phishing patterns
Generation of realistic spear-phishing templates
Supports awareness training and attack simulation
Research-backed approach (published work)

🛠️ Tech Stack
Python
Selenium (Web scraping & automation)
Scikit-learn / ML models
Pandas, NumPy
Jupyter Notebook

⚙️ How It Works
Collects publicly available user data using Selenium
Cleans and preprocesses the dataset
Applies ML algorithms to classify behavior patterns
Generates targeted phishing templates based on insights

📊 Use Cases
Cybersecurity awareness training
Phishing simulation exercises
Research in social engineering attacks
Defensive security testing

🔐 Security & Ethics
This project is built strictly for educational and defensive purposes.
No real attacks are conducted. Data usage follows ethical guidelines.

📚 Research
Findings presented at an international conference
Published in Springer to support cybersecurity awareness

📌 Future Improvements
Improve ML model accuracy with larger datasets
Integrate real-time detection capabilities
Add phishing detection dashboard

